520. Reference our telegram 615, November 21, 6 p.m.;
Foreign Relations, 1939, vol. iii, p. 596. 633, November 27, midnight [noon?];
Ibid., p. 599. 650, December 2, 6 p.m., 1939.Not printed. A completely trustworthy American citizen has recently had an interview with “Mr. X”Yoshisuke Aikawa, Japanese industrialist. in Hsinking, Manchuria, in the course of which the latter expressed views substantially as follows.
